---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CareerTimeline from "../components/about/CareerTimeline.astro";
import SkillsGrid from "../components/about/SkillsGrid.astro";
import Education from "../components/about/Education.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Nancy Chauhan" description="Developer Relations Engineer at Arize AI. CNCF Ambassador, Women in Cloud Native founder. Love to build, ship, and teach.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 pt-10 md:pt-14 pb-20">

    {/* Hero: Bio + Photo */}
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_auto] gap-6 lg:gap-6 mb-16 animate-on-scroll">
      <div>
        <p class="font-mono text-xs text-[var(--color-stone-400)] mb-3">$ cat about.md</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold font-sans tracking-tight mb-5">
          About Me<span class="text-[var(--color-purple)]">.</span>
        </h1>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-base font-sans text-[var(--color-stone-600)] leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
          <p>
            Having worked across <strong class="text-[var(--color-stone-900)]">Engineering, Product, and Developer Relations</strong>, I've had the opportunity to look at technology from different perspectives. I started by hacking through software engineering problems and building solutions that improve software reliability. Over time, I found myself becoming equally curious about the people using those solutions, their problems, their needs, and how an idea could be shaped into a useful product.
          </p>
          <p>
            That curiosity naturally led me toward <span class="text-[var(--color-purple)]">Product and Developer Relations</span>, where I could bring together my interest in technology, education, and building products 💜. I enjoy understanding user problems, shaping ideas from ideation to execution, and breaking down complex technical concepts into easier, more accessible content.
          </p>
          <details class="group">
            <summary class="cursor-pointer list-none inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-purple)] hover:underline select-none">
              <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-90" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
              </svg>
              Read more
            </summary>
            <div class="mt-5 space-y-5">
              <p>
                On a more personal note, I'm incredibly thankful for everyone I've met through open source and the broader community ✨. I come from a non-CS background, and in many ways, <strong class="text-[var(--color-stone-900)]">open source has been my university</strong>. The people I've met, including mentors, collaborators, and friends, have taught me so much, and I continue to be inspired by their support and generosity.
                I always say that the community is the best part of tech, and I've never been wrong.
              </p>
              <p>
                Outside of work, I love traveling, meeting new people, exploring museums, learning about history, art, and culture, and trying local food from every country I visit. I'm also into making digital illustrations and zines, cycling to clear my head, and reading about psychology, new tech, and how society is constantly changing.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Photo - sticky on desktop */}
      <div class="flex justify-center lg:justify-end lg:sticky lg:top-24 lg:self-start">
        <div class="card-brutal p-0 overflow-hidden w-[260px] md:w-[300px]">
          <img
            src="/nancy-paris.jpg"
            alt="Nancy Chauhan"
            class="w-full aspect-[3/4] object-cover object-[25%_center]"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <div class="border-t-2 border-[var(--color-stone-800)] px-4 py-3">
            <p class="font-mono text-xs text-[var(--color-stone-400)]">$ nancy --connect --location="SF"<span class="terminal-cursor"></span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* Work */}
    <div class="mb-20">
      <CareerTimeline />
    </div>

    {/* Tech Stack */}
    <div class="mb-20">
      <SkillsGrid />
    </div>

    {/* Education */}
    <div>
      <Education />
    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
